<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,222,684]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
<keyLead pageId="9" pageNumber="210">1. Male genital capsule with a stout, apically rounded tubercle on left side, tubercle rarely more spinelike, but never visible in dorsal aspect; body oval to elongate oval................................................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,222,684]" box="[151,1436,281,303]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,281,303]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">– Male genital capsule with an elongate apically pointed spine on left side, often visible in dorsal aspect; body elongate oval. 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,222,684]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
<keyLead pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
2. Uniformly dull black, often flattened, species (
<figureCitation box="[683,803,310,332]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–54" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1866,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 43–54. Laterospinocoris and Nigrotomocoris spp. 43, L. cyaneipennis (Reuter), male (dorsal aspect). 44, L. cyaneipennis, male (lateral aspect). 45, L. cyaneipennis, female (dorsal aspect). 46, L. mexicanus, n. sp., male (dorsal aspect). 47, L. mexicanus, n. sp., male (lateral aspect). 48, L. mexicanus, n. sp., female (dorsal aspect). 49, N. keltoni, n. sp., male (dorsal aspect). 50, N. keltoni, n. sp., male (lateral aspect). 51, N. keltoni, n. sp., female (dorsal aspect). 52, N. longirostris, n. sp., male (dorsal aspect). 53, N. longirostris, n. sp., male (lateral aspect). 54, N. longirostris, n. sp., female (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3816474" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3816474/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">Figs. 50, 53</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[814,841,310,332]" captionStart="FIGURES 55–66" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1793,1818]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@35.[151,1436,181,1767]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 55–66. Nigrotomocoris and Schaffnerocoris spp. 55, N. nigrus (Carvalho), male (dorsal aspect). 56, N. nigrus, male (lateral aspect). 57, N. nigrus, female (dorsal aspect). 58, N. tibiopallidus (Carvalho), male (dorsal aspect). 59, N. tibiopallidus, male (lateral aspect). 60, N. tibiopallidus, female (dorsal aspect). 61, S. fuscotibialis, n. sp., male (dorsal aspect). 62, S. fuscotibialis, n. sp., male (lateral aspect). 63, S. pallipes, n. sp., male (dorsal aspect). 64, S. pallipes, n. sp., female (dorsal aspect). 65, S. similis, n. sp., male (dorsal aspect). 66, S. similis, n. sp., male (lateral aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3816476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3816476/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">56</figureCitation>
); right paramere broadly rounded or spatulate apically (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 104–112" captionStartId="43.[151,264,1666,1691]" captionTargetBox="[183,1407,184,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[177,1411,181,1641]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 104–112. Male genitalia of Nigrotomocoris spp. N. keltoni, n. sp.: 104, endosoma. 105, left paramere. 106, right paramere. N. longirosris, n. sp.: 107, left paramere. 108, right paramere. N. nigrus: 109, left paramere. 110, right paramere. N. tibiopallidus: 111, left paramere. 112, right paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3816488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3816488/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">Figs. 106, 108, 110, 112</figureCitation>
)................................................................. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1202,1436,339,361]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
<taxonomicName authority="Henry &amp; Menard, 2020" authorityName="Henry &amp; Menard" authorityYear="2020" box="[1202,1357,339,360]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Nigrotomocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
