</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1369,1436,340,361]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,222,684]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
<keyLead pageId="9" pageNumber="210">– Multicolored species, head and pronotum often yellow or orange, contrasting with a darker hemelytron, often with a bluish sheen; right paramere never spatulate apically................................................................3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,222,684]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
<keyLead pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
