ale (dorsal aspect). 33, A. roseus, n. sp., male (lateral aspect). 34, A. roseus, female (dorsal aspect). 35, A. rostratus, n. sp., male (dorsal aspect). 36, A. rostratus, n. sp., male (lateral aspect). 37, A. rostratus, n. sp., female (dorsal aspect). 38, A. schaffneri, n. sp., male (dorsal aspect). 39, A. schaffneri, n. sp., male (lateral aspect). 40, A. schaffneri n. sp., female (dorsal aspect). 41, A. scutellatus n. sp., male (dorsal aspect). 42, A. scutellatus, n. sp., female (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3816468" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3816470" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3816472" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3816468/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3816470/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/3816472/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">Figs. 11–42</figureCitation>
), inner margin of eye level with outer anterior margin of pronotum; calli prominent (
<figureCitation box="[388,482,457,479]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–7" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1538,1563]" captionTargetBox="[225,1361,381,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[225,1361,381,1513]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2–7. Scanning electron microscope (SEM) micrographs of Agaveocoris agavis. 2, head and pronotum, dorsal aspect. 3, head and pronotum, lateral aspect. 4, head, frontal aspect. 5, metathoracic scent gland opening and ostiolar evaporative area. 6, genital capsule, showing right and left paramere and tubercle, caudal aspect. 7, genital capsule, showing right paramere and tubercle, lateral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3816466" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3816466/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">Figs. 2–4</figureCitation>
), strongly raised with a depression between; right paramere with a distinct upturned hook at apex (
<figureCitation box="[233,385,486,508]" captionStart="FIGURES 67–77" captionStartId="36.[151,264,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,191,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[176,1411,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 67–77. Male genitalia of Caulotops and Agaveocoris spp. Caulotops platensis: 67, genital capsule. 68, left paramere. 69, right paramere. Agaveocoris agavis: 70, endosoma. 71, left paramere. 72, right paramere. A. barberi: 73, left paramere. 74, right paramere. A. barrerai, n. sp.: 75, left paramere. 76, right paramere. A. bimaculatus, n. sp.: 77, endosoma. 78, left paramere. 79, right paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3816478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3816478/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">Figs. 72, 74, 76</figureCitation>
, 79).................................................................... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1236,1436,486,507]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
<taxonomicName authority="Henry &amp; Menard, 2020" authorityName="Henry &amp; Menard" authorityYear="2020" box="[1236,1357,486,507]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Agaveocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1236,1357,486,507]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">Agaveocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1369,1436,486,507]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,222,684]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
<keyLead pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
– Mostly short, round species; eyes less produced, level of inner margin of each eye well inside outer anterior margin of prono- tum; calli flat, not strongly raised; apex of right paramere acute, without an upturned process....... 
<taxonomicName authority="Townsend" authorityName="Townsend" authorityYear="1892" box="[1205,1436,544,566]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Halticotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
